The United States expresses deep sadness over the recent earthquake in Afghanistan that claimed the lives of at least 1,000 people. President Biden is closely monitoring the situation and has instructed USAID and other federal government partners to evaluate potential response options to assist those most impacted by the disaster. As the largest donor of humanitarian aid to Afghanistan, the United States is already providing medical care and shelter supplies through its humanitarian partners on the ground. The US remains committed to supporting the Afghan people during and after this devastating event.